+Generate `throws` parameter correctly
+
+While reworking the formatting and imports generation systems I noticed that we don't handle `throws="1"` correctly in all paths - if there we no parameters, we'd not add the error parameter. This PR fixes that.
+
+Example that reproduces the issue:
+
+```go
+package main
+
+import (
+	"fmt"
+
+	"codeberg.org/puregotk/puregotk/v4/gio"
+)
+
+func main() {
+	c := gio.NewCancellable()
+	c.Cancel()
+
+	_, err := c.SetErrorIfCancelled()
+	fmt.Println("error:", err)
+}
+```
+
+On `main`:
+
+```shell
+$ go run ./cmd/throws-verification/
+error: <nil>
+```
+
+On this branch the error is thrown correctly:
+
+```shell
+$ go run ./cmd/throws-verification/
+error: Gtk reported an error with message: 'Operation was cancelled', domain: '59' and code: '19'
+```
+
+Rework formatting and import generation
+
+Blocked by https://codeberg.org/puregotk/puregotk/pulls/46
+
+On `main`, running `./gen.sh` is quite slow:
+
+```shell
+$ time ./gen.sh 
+generating go files...
+making sure imports are correct...
+formatting files...
+running a second pass for goimports...
+running go vet...
+# ...
+
+real    1m1.772s
+user    1m11.937s
+sys     0m35.716s
+```
+
+It's slow mostly because of `goimports`, which has to scan every single file in order to add the imports. `gofumpt` is also called in `gen.sh`, not in the generator.
+
+This PR improves the generation speed quite significantly; `./gen.sh` takes just a little ~4s:
+
+```shell
+pojntfx@node-1w7jr9qswe5jsmcgqsxbjtnc4:~/Projects/puregotk-neo$ time ./gen.sh 
+generating go files...
+running go vet...
+# ...
+
+real    0m3.030s
+user    0m3.775s
+sys     0m0.459s
+```
+
+This is done with two changes (see the individual commits):
+
+1) Calling `gofumpt` in-process through the Go API instead of by spawning a subprocess
+2) Tracking imports while we're generating the bindings, and then adding them in the template instead of letting `goimports` handle them
+
+I've taken special care to make sure that generating 3rd-party libraries doesn't break; see the changes to `examples/`. The new `Dependency` struct can be used to explicitly map external GIR namespaces to the relevant Go packages.
+
+I already re-ran the script - there are no changes in the generated code, except for formatting in one of the examples - it looks like the state on `main` wasn't formatted properly.
